events.name: IoT Garage Prague
events.description:
We would like to invite you to the first IoT Garage in Prague!

IoT Garage is a regular *punk* meetup for Internet of Things and Open Hardware fans and enthusiasts.

IoT Garage Prague is happening regularly once per month at the same date (every second Wednesday of a month) and place (Juicymo HQ).

It is a place where you can come and play or tinker with Open Hardware or Internet of Things. A place where you can discover, learn or explore new things and technologies.

You do not need to have any previous knowledge or you can be a hardware or software guru.

You can bring your own project and discus it or continue its development. Or you can come and find out what that strange Arduino or RaspberryPi is all about.

We have some robots which need some programming love. We have some lonely Arduinos and Raspies which desire to be connected and plugged into some cool project. We have a (Open Hardware!) 3D printer which can give life to cases of your projects.

We do not sell anything and entire IoT Garage is a non-profit effort meant to spread the knowledge about the wonderful world of Open Hardware and Internet of Things - while having great fun doing so.

IoT Garage is organized by GDG Prague with the responsible organizer Tomáš Jukin (there is a team behing IoT Garage Prague, but when something is not right, Tom is here to be blamed :-D). IoT Garage Prague is proudly supported by Juicymo to which we thanks for gadgets and space.

IoT Garage is a "Open Source Event" (heavily inspired by the successful GDG Garage event series invented by Filip Hráček) - which means that we encourage you to fork us! Feel free to ask us about any information regarding the organization of our event.

IoT Garage is intended to be small regular event (space capacity is 15 people).

And yes we plan some bigger IoT and Open Hardware hackathons in future!

We can discus English or Czech with you at IoT Garage.

We have internet connection, electricity and gadgets, you are encouraged to bring a notebook with you.

GDG Developers Event: 
https://developers.google.com/events/5048642981593088/

GUG.cz Website Event:
http://www.gug.cz/cs/akce/iot-garage-prague
events.how_to_find_us: You can reach us by from metro B "Karlovo náměstí", metro C "I. P. Pavlova" or metro A "Náměstí Míru", then by tram 22 to a station Krymská, then 3 mins on foot

events.description:
REGISTER HERE: http://bit.ly/gameecon

[EN]
GUG.cz together with Gamee, O2, CzechCrunch and MSD IT are preparing second all-day playful conference focused on web development and mostly HTML5 & JS games. You can get in touch with interesting technologies, rich program full of practically focused presentations and workshops at this event. We focus on new trends in HTML5, JavaScript and our frontend ninjas explain you, what is currently the best way how to build cool apps.

Event takes place in building FIVE, in newly opened spaces by MSD IT Global Innovation Center. It’s located right across Riverview building, entrance is from street Na Valentince.

______________________________________________________________________

GUG.cz ve spolupráci s Gamee, O2, CzechCrunch a MSD IT připravuje už druhou celodenní hravou konferenci se zaměřením na webový vývoj a především frontend webových aplikací a HTML5 & JS her. Bohatý program plný nejen prakticky zaměřených přednášek, ale také workshopů Ti umožní si zajímavé technologie osahat přímo na místě. events.name: Ivan Kutil- Google Apps Script = G Suite(automatizace || integrace || rozšíření)
events.description:
Google Apps Script je nástroj pro rozšíření Google aplikací, integraci služeb a automatizaci práce v G Suite.
K dispozici je od roku 2009 (=dříve serverless bylo cool) a za tu dobu prošel dlouhou cestu, která není stále u konce a má před sebou velkou světlou budoucnost. Pomocí online editoru, jazyka JavaScriptu a připravených funkcí vázaných na Google API je téměř kdokoliv schopen vytvořit rychlou aplikaci či skript.
Nedávno se přidala podpora pro tvorbu botů v Hangouts Chat API, na kterou se také letmo podíváme.

Ivan patří k nejzkušenějším odborníkům na firemní služby Google v ČR. Profesionálně se jeho technologiím věnuje od roku 2008, kdy programoval první iGoogle Gadgety na zakázku. V roce 2011 spoluzaložil společnost AppSatori (http://appsatori.eu/), která je lídrem v oblasti custom vývoje automatizačních řešení pro G Suite. Na starosti má vývoj a konzultace řešení postavených na Google Cloud
Od roku 2013 je zařazen do elitního programu Google Developer Expert na technologii Google Apps Script.
Své znalosti prezentuje na českých a zahraničních konferencí nebo formou článků na svém blogu http://kutil.org .
V poslední době se zajímá o témata spojená s machine learningem

events.name: Peter Malina & Vojtech Mašek - Angular 101 - jsDevMeetup
events.description:
Angular 101 je workshop pro začátečníky s frameworkem Angular. Během přednášky pokryjeme základy jako jsou komponenty, servisy a moduly ale také pokročilejší témata jako nastavení routování a HTTP klienta. Workshop bude rozdělen na dvě části:
- Architektura a návrh Angularu
- Živé kódování jednoduchých komponent

V případě zájmu si můžete přinést svoje počítače a pokud budete chtít, můžete se držet živého kódování na plátně. Workshop je ideální pro nováčky v Angularu se základy JavaScriptu nebo TypeScriptu.

Petr Malina
Petr je CTO ve FlowUp, softwarové firmy založené v Brně a vytvářející cloudové nativní webové aplikace a systémy za použití Golang, Python a Angular. Považuje se za pionýra v nových technologiích a miluje automatizaci a cloudové technologie.

Vojtech Mašek
Vojtech je vedoucí vývojář ve FlowUp. Vede týmy k naplnění jejich cílů. Má rád čistou architekturu a kód, který sleduje moderní trendy frontendového vývoje. Je technologický nadšenec se zkušeností v Angularu a TypeScriptu.

ENGLISH
------------------------------------------------
Angular 101 is an introductory workshop to the Angular framework. We'll cover all basics suchas components, services and modules, as well as more complex features like routing configuration and HTTP client. The workshop will be split into two parts:
-Architecture and design of Angular
-Live coding simple components

Please feel free to bring your own laptops if you want to follow along with our live coding. The workshop is ideal for newcomers to Angular with a JavaScript and/or Typescript background.

Peter Malina

events.name: Actions on Google: Adi Mazor - Talk to me: Tips and Best Practice for Voice UI
events.description:
We are thrilled to announce an amazing speaker all the way from Izrael, who accepted our invitation and it's coming to see us in Prague - Adi Mazor Kario, MSc Cognitive Science, GDE, Sprint Master, Experience Expert.

Adi is a Senior UX expert, Product and Voice Designer. She is also a Google mentor and expert in the future of technology. She is the owner and CEO of Wizard Product Design & UX.
With more than 17 years of experience, Adi created projects for fortune 500 companies, like Intel and IBM in parallel to smaller companies and startups by guiding them from idea and strategy to an amazing user experience that sells more.
Since 2016 Adi has been teaching and practicing Voice UX and she enjoys being part of the future. She believes Voice Design is the most exciting & promising fields of User Experience today!

Voice Design is a probably the most exciting & promising fields of User experience today! Conversational apps enable users an emotional, natural connection with applications and brands.
The dream of talking freely to machines becomes a reality in the last few years. Conversational interfaces or assistants usage is growing and entering every household- Apple revealed people talk to Siri as a therapist and Amazon created “listen with Alexa” to reads bedtime stories to young kids. In the last year alone the user base of voice devices grew by 129% and experts predict that by[masked]% of interfaces will be speech recognition based. How will this tech change affect our lives, our culture and the future of our kids? How could we create great Voice applications that engage users and clients with our brand and product?

During the talk we will discuss the future of voice technologies, whats special in this technology and how can we design awesome voice experiences.

Interested in hands-on experience? The following day is Adi's workshop: https://www.meetup.com/GDGPrague/events/252327365/

Connect with her: https://www.linkedin.com/in/adimazorkario/

Adi Mazor Kario, MSc Cognitive Science, GDE, Sprint Master, Experience Expert. (see the talk event for full bio)

Design sprint is a short collaborative process for answering critical business & product questions through design, prototyping, and testing. In this hands-on, fast-paced workshop we will collaborate in small groups and learn how to turn a business idea into a natural, fun and engaging conversation between a user and an assistant. Adi is a Certified Google Sprint Masters and she loves conducting designs since they are enjoyable and energetic - so come with good vibes :)

events.name: DevFest CZ 2018
events.description:
DevFest CZ 2018 will take you to another time!
Tickets available at https://2018.devfest.cz/

What is DevFest?
A community-organized festival of developers and true geeks.
- 2 days
- Multiple tracks and a special Women track
- Interactive themed game
- International speakers
- A few hundreds of attendees
- Geeky afterparty

What’s new this year?
Last year, we brought DevFest CZ back to Prague. This year, we decided to go back in time and see the city through different eyes. Medieval eyes! You can look forward to a specially crafted gamification with this theme.
We also heard out your feedback and decided to change some things around. So this year, it’s Friday for the workshops, Saturday for the talks and Sunday for resting (after the afterparty).

Basic info:
Date: 26–27 October, 2018
Venue: Pragovka, Prague
Language: English, Czech
Topics: Web, Android, Firebase, Angular, Soft skills, Cloud, PWA, IoT and more
Tickets: available on www.devfest.cz

Connect with us!
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/DevFestCZ
Twitter: https://twitter.com/DevFest_CZ
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/devfestcz/
Web: https://2018.devfest.cz/

See you in Prague...
...And DevFest for All!
